  <locationDescription><![CDATA[<p>A multi-centre holiday lets you combine multiple destinations and exciting activities to create your ideal trip. Enjoy everything from panoramic walks, cultural tours and outdoor adventures to relaxing days and tasty local cuisine.</p>
<h3>Discover the wild and beautiful Lake Bohinj</h3>
<p>Wander the forested shores, admire the rugged mountains and enjoy the untamed nature that surrounds Lake Bohinj. Much of the walking is quite easy-going, meandering between traditional villages, meadows, waterfalls and caves and there are plenty of challenges for keener hikers too. The gondola up Mount Vogel takes you to the best viewpoints and the start points for some really impressive hikes, or head to the idyllic Pokljuka Plateau to explore pretty alpine meadows strewn with traditional wooden farm buildings. Back at the lake, take to the water by romantic wooden boat, or test your balance on a paddleboard - there are some lovely spots for a lakeside picnic and refreshing dip in the clear waters too. The famously photogenic Lake Bled is around 20 minutes' away by train, or 40 by bus and is worth a day trip to see it's iconic island and pletna boats.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/b56bdaf2399f46828fa1f01256cae753" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b56bdaf2399f46828fa1f01256cae753}" title="Lake Bohinj" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Bohinj</a></p>
<h3>Hike in the Soča Valley from Bovec</h3>
<p>Bovec sits in the picturesque Soča Valley, on the edge of the strikingly blue River Soča, which gushes through gorges and over waterfalls, having spent years carving unique and impressive formations in the rock. This is where you need to come if you want the wow-factor - the scenery around this part of Slovenia is spectacular and Bovec is a fantastic hub for exploring the great outdoors. Walk a section of the Juliana Trail, or discover the Soča River by kayak or paddleboard. Put your leg muscles to the test on a mountain bike, or ease your way to the best viewpoints on an e-bike. Visit the majestic Kluže fortress above the Koritnica gorge - it's one of the most visited cultural sights in the valley - or head to the Kobarid Museum to learn more about the history of the area.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/7cc8e45320754ead8a9f026b9de3f1ad" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7cc8e45320754ead8a9f026b9de3f1ad}" title="Bovec" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Bovec</a></p>
<h3>Explore Kranjska Gora</h3>
<p>Kranjska Gora is in a picture-perfect location between the forested foothills and limestone peaks of the Julian Alps, close to the Austrian and Italian borders. Walk to the triple-border point, explore the cobbled streets and pretty alpine meadows. Take a dip in Lake Jasna, ride the alpine coaster down from the top of the Vitranc chairlift, or try zip-lining at Planica. The walking around Kranjska Gora is stunning, with panoramic views at every turn - easy strolls along the river, wander the boardwalks along the wetlands at the Zelenci Nature Park, or take on a challenge amongst the most dramatic scenery in the area on a high mountain hike starting from the top of the Vršič Pass.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab" href="/{localLink:umb://document/9b6cf6eac79541f5850e141e41a071ab}" title="Kranjska Gora" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Kranjska Gora</a></p>
<p><a href="tel:01483791111" class="InfinityNumber c-btn">Call Us to Book Today</a></p>
<p><em>Please note: This is an independent multi-centre holiday and you are free to choose your own itinerary in each destination. The above contains recommendations which are provided for information only and are not included in the price of your holiday. An Inghams Representative will be on hand locally either in resort or by telephone and will provide advice and offer optional excursions and walking passes.</em></p>
<p><em>Places are limited and cannot be guaranteed. Special diets, including vegetarian, must be requested prior to booking.</em></p>
<p><em>The itineraries may be subject to change. Where this becomes necessary, and where practicable, we will take the steps as outlined in clause 5 of our <a data-udi="umb://document/b703ff07ccec43baad41fffcfcc61821" href="/{localLink:umb://document/b703ff07ccec43baad41fffcfcc61821}" title="Terms &amp; Conditions">terms and conditions</a>.</em></p>
<h4>Your holiday excludes:</h4>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Any suggestions of things to do made in the itinerary – these are provided for information only</li>
<li>Luggage transport – luggage is taken with you on the transfers</li>
<li>Any extras, drinks, gratuities and personal expenses</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>]]></locationDescription>
